==English==
==Etymology==
From Latin liber meaning free.

===Adjective===

# Generous in quantity.
#: ''Add a '''liberal''' sprinkling of salt.''
# Lacking morals.
# Not strict.
#: ''Her parents had '''liberal''' ideas about child-rearing.''
# Favoring ideas of civil liberties, equal justice, individual participation in government. 
# (''US'') Pertaining to the Democratic Party.
# (''UK'') Pertaining to the [[Liberal Democrat]]s.
# Supporting a Liberal political party.
===Noun===
'''liberal'''

# One who is liberal.
# One who is open minded.
# One who is not orthodox.
# A supporter of Liberalism
